<h2 id=3D"3">odoc 3.2.1 release</h2>
<div class=3D"outline-text-2" id=3D"text-3">
<p>
Archive: <a href=3D"https://discuss.ocaml.org/t/ann-odoc-3-2-1-release/1808=
8/1">https://discuss.ocaml.org/t/ann-odoc-3-2-1-release/18088/1</a>
</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"outline-container-org89347aa" class=3D"outline-3">
<h3 id=3D"org89347aa">Jon Ludlam announced</h3>
<div class=3D"outline-text-3" id=3D"text-org89347aa">
<p>
The odoc team is pleased to announce the release of odoc 3.2.1!
</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"outline-container-orge848e97" class=3D"outline-4">
<h4 id=3D"orge848e97">Highlights</h4>
<div class=3D"outline-text-4" id=3D"text-orge848e97">
</div>
<ul class=3D"org-ul">
<li><a id=3D"org2974336"></a>OCaml 5.5.0 support<br />
<div class=3D"outline-text-5" id=3D"text-org2974336">
<p>
odoc now compiles against, and produces documentation for, OCaml 5.5.0 (@pa=
nglesd, @xvw, <a href=3D"https://github.com/ocaml/odoc/issues/1406">#1406</=
a>).
</p>
</div>
</li>
<li><a id=3D"orgb5efb46"></a>OxCaml support<br />
<div class=3D"outline-text-5" id=3D"text-orgb5efb46">
<p>
odoc now supports OxCaml natively, thanks to @lukemaurer and @art-w (<a hre=
f=3D"https://github.com/ocaml/odoc/issues/1399">#1399</a>). Right now this =
is very bare-bones, but full support for the various features of OxCaml is =
already in progress. If you're interested, check out the <a href=3D"https:/=
/github.com/ocaml/odoc/pulls">PRs</a>!
</p>

<p>
One thing worth flagging: because OxCaml is moving much faster than upstrea=
m OCaml, each odoc release will likely support only a single OxCaml release=
, in contrast to our usual policy of supporting every OCaml back to 4.08. I=
f you're documenting an OxCaml project, please use a matched pair of odoc a=
nd oxcaml-compiler.
</p>
</div>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div id=3D"outline-container-org414e2e9" class=3D"outline-4">
<h4 id=3D"org414e2e9">Added</h4>
<div class=3D"outline-text-4" id=3D"text-org414e2e9">
<ul class=3D"org-ul">
<li>Persistent LaTeX macros in the HTML/KaTeX backend (@dlesbre, <a href=3D=
"https://github.com/ocaml/odoc/issues/1391">#1391</a>).</li>
<li>The <code>markdown-generate</code> command now accepts multiple <code>.=
odocl</code> files in a single invocation, so you no longer need to wrap it=
 in a shell loop (@davesnx, <a href=3D"https://github.com/ocaml/odoc/issues=
/1387">#1387</a>).</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div id=3D"outline-container-org920334f" class=3D"outline-4">
<h4 id=3D"org920334f">Changed / Fixed</h4>
<div class=3D"outline-text-4" id=3D"text-org920334f">
<ul class=3D"org-ul">
<li>Fixed two long-standing compile-time crashes, <a href=3D"https://github=
.com/ocaml/odoc/issues/930">#930</a> and #1385 (@jonludlam, <a href=3D"http=
s://github.com/ocaml/odoc/issues/1400">#1400</a>).</li>
<li>The Markdown backend now assumes <code>ocaml</code> as the language id =
on declarations, and collects code snippets into a single block with commen=
ts rather than splitting variants/records per constructor/field.</li>
<li>URL remapping now works correctly for page references (@jonludlam, <a h=
ref=3D"https://github.com/ocaml/odoc/issues/1395">#1395</a>).</li>
<li>Incremental builds no longer break under the conditions described in <a=
 href=3D"https://github.com/ocaml/odoc/issues/1396">#1396</a> (@jonludlam, =
<a href=3D"https://github.com/ocaml/odoc/issues/1402">#1402</a>).</li>
<li><code>--warn-error</code> now reliably promotes all warnings to errors =
(@jonludlam, <a href=3D"https://github.com/ocaml/odoc/issues/1402">#1402</a=
>).</li>
<li>Polymorphic arguments are no longer missing their parentheses (@art-w, =
<a href=3D"https://github.com/ocaml/odoc/issues/1404">#1404</a>).</li>
<li>Fixed a regression that broke docs for packages depending on ~base ~und=
er OCaml 5.5.0 (@jonludlam, <a href=3D"https://github.com/ocaml/odoc/issues=
/1426">#1426</a>, <a href=3D"https://github.com/ocaml/odoc/issues/1427">#14=
27</a>).</li>
<li>Fixed a regression that broke docs for packages depending on <code>merl=
in-lib</code> (@jonludlam, <a href=3D"https://github.com/ocaml/odoc/issues/=
1429">#1429</a>, <a href=3D"https://github.com/ocaml/odoc/issues/1430">#143=
0</a>).</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div id=3D"outline-container-org27765e0" class=3D"outline-4">
<h4 id=3D"org27765e0">Installation</h4>
<div class=3D"outline-text-4" id=3D"text-org27765e0">
<pre class=3D"example" id=3D"orgc63d29f">
opam update
opam install odoc
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div id=3D"outline-container-org6a0c80b" class=3D"outline-4">
<h4 id=3D"org6a0c80b">Use</h4>
<div class=3D"outline-text-4" id=3D"text-org6a0c80b">
<p>
Please use <a href=3D"https://ocaml.github.io/odoc/odoc-driver/index.html">=
odoc_driver</a> to build and test your package's docs locally and to see ho=
w they will look on ocaml.org.
</p>

<p>
Odig and Dune continue to work as before, no changes required. Full support=
 for all of the features of odoc 3.x is being worked on in Dune.
</p>
</div>
</div>
